text: Edvard Jansson (10 September 1888 - 18 February 1929) was a Finnish gymnast. He competed in the men's artistic individual all-around event at the 1912 Summer Olympics. ==References== Category:1888 births Category:1929 deaths Category:Finnish male artistic gymnasts Category:Olympic gymnasts of Finland Category:Gymnasts at the 1912 Summer Olympics Category:People from Lohja
